    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-07-20</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-09-25T17:51:42Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Regional Innovation Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill establishes a Regional Technology and Innovation Hub Program and a Regional Clean Energy Innovation Program. </p> <p>The bill directs the Department of Commerce to establish the Regional Technology and Innovation Hub Program to</p> <ul> <li> encourage collaboration among local, state, and federal government entities, institutions of higher education, the private sector, nonprofit organizations, and others to promote inclusive regional innovation initiatives; </li> <li> designate eligible consortia as hubs and facilitate activities by such consortia in implementing their regional innovation strategies; and </li> <li>develop best practices for regional development and competitiveness in technology and innovation. </li> </ul> <p>Additionally, the Department of Energy shall establish the Regional Clean Energy Innovation Program to</p> <ul> <li>enhance the economic, environmental, and energy security of the United States; </li> <li>accelerate the pace of innovation of clean energy technologies through regional clean energy innovation partnerships;</li> <li>improve the competitiveness of U.S. clean energy technology research, development, demonstration, and commercial application; and</li> <li>support the development of tools and technologies best suited for use in diverse regions of the United States, including in rural, tribal, and low-income communities.</li> </ul>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>07</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2022-02-28</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2022-03-09T16:18:11Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Regional Innovation Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill establishes a Regional Technology and Innovation Hub Program and a Regional Clean Energy Innovation Program. </p> <p>The bill directs the Department of Commerce to establish the Regional Technology and Innovation Hub Program to</p> <ul> <li> encourage collaboration among local, state, and federal government entities, institutions of higher education, the private sector, nonprofit organizations, and others to promote inclusive regional innovation initiatives; </li> <li> designate eligible consortia as hubs and facilitate activities by such consortia in implementing their regional innovation strategies; and </li> <li>develop best practices for regional development and competitiveness in technology and innovation. </li> </ul> <p>Additionally, the Department of Energy shall establish the Regional Clean Energy Innovation Program to</p> <ul> <li>enhance the economic, environmental, and energy security of the United States; </li> <li>accelerate the pace of innovation of clean energy technologies through regional clean energy innovation partnerships;</li> <li>improve the competitiveness of U.S. clean energy technology research, development, demonstration, and commercial application; and </li> <li>support the development of tools and technologies best suited for use in diverse regions of the United States, including in rural, tribal, and low-income communities.</li> </ul> <p>Commerce shall carry out a program of data collection and analysis of technology and innovation sectors critical to realizing national objectives, including national security, economic prosperity, and social welfare.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
